Template-based code generation for ~if transform

The template lookup system works (320_018, 320_019 pass), but using templates
from within stdlib modules has an import resolution issue. When control.kz
imports template.kz and then tries to use ~std.template:define, the event
is not found in the registry.

This is a deeper issue with how stdlib modules are loaded and how imports
are resolved during parsing. The workaround for now is using hardcoded
code generation in the transform (which test 320_020 validates).

TO FIX:
1. Investigate why ~import in stdlib modules doesn't make events available
2. Consider defining stdlib templates in a pre-loaded location
3. Or fix the import resolution order for nested stdlib imports
